pull_request.title: Create build-android.sh
pull_request.body:
This script allows for cross-compiling for Android. I've only tested it on Ubuntu WSL, where it works perfectly. Allows configuration of ABI, minimum SDK version, and build output directory. Can be called from root repo directory by "scripts/build-android.sh" or from scripts directory by "./build-android.sh." 
For x86 and x86_64 ABI builds, it is necessary to comment out lines 3-5 of ".CMake/add-cpu-extension-flags.cmake" with try_run function to prevent the build system attempting to it when it's compiled for another target.

pull_request.title: Update CMakeLists.txt C flags for Android
pull_request.body: Run options which break Android build only if the target system is not Android
